review_blob: I bought this beer becasue I was intrigued by the squat bottle and in the mood for something new. I found it to have a rich think flavor with a bready after taste.
The bllueberry aroma is very nice and the flavor is very light and sweet, almost watery, but nice.
Smooth and not too bitter. As surprising it may seem, this beer goes extremely well with Indian cuisine.
This is one of the worst "Bock"s I have ever had. The flavor is weak and disappointing.
This is a nice dark neer with a light caramel flavor and a deep colored apperance.
This is a good beer with Thai food. The flavor is light and a bit fruity. It actually tastes like the smoke from apricot tabbacco.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Its a great drink when you are in the mood for a light flavor. Its very crisp and a bit sour.
Icehouse is watery and has an odd, but weak flavor. It is not a very good beer.
This is one of the best stouts I have ever had. It is great with any food and has a very creamy finish.
This beer is light and virtually flavorless. It tastes much like Rolling Rock.
I love the Guinness Extra Stout with anything. It has strong flavor and creamy finish.
This beer is great with a  bit of lime and also with spicey food. It is my avorite for a Mexican eatery.
